&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: geist, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: geist, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Zoro.com is a leading eCommerce platform offering nearly 12 million tools, parts and supplies for our business customers. Launched in 2011, we brought a B2C-like experience to the B2B industry, and continue to be at the forefront of digital innovation at the intersection of technology and distribution. We have rapidly grown to over $1 billion in annual revenue and we’re just getting started!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Function:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Zoro, we desire to have every product for every business need. Associate Category Managers are key contributors to our growth in both sales and category expansion. The Category Management team is responsible for defining strategies for our key categories and then finding and managing supplier relationships that allow us to add products and drive growth in those categories.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An Associate Category Manager’s success will be defined by helping operationalize and accelerate the sales of the existing portfolio of products. The Associate Category Manager is responsible for supporting aligned Category Managers analyzing the business and executing tactics for assigned categories.&amp;nbsp; This position will work in a team environment with a focus on developing insights, identifying opportunities and communicating recommendations to lead future industry growth to our internal partners and external suppliers. In addition, they will drive and support activities that help Zoro sell more products and manage cost and profitability. The Associate Category Manager will execute reporting and analysis to support assigned product categories to inform on category and supplier performance, collaborate closely with cross-functional partners throughout the business, and participate in supplier relationship management. The Associate Category Manager will be a key liaison with internal partners to help drive customer experience and sales performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, manage and update reports regarding new suppliers, SKU productivity, sales performance, and assortment gaps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continually and proactively monitor the financial performance of categories and suppliers to measure against the category product strategies and KPI’s to ensure we are providing an awesome customer experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify areas within aligned categories for product expansion and product optimization. Take ownership over identified expansion and optimization activities with support of CM and/or Sr. CM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with suppliers to acquire comprehensive product information including product specifications, product images, pricing information, and additional product content; This effort will require cross-functional partnership as well as direct supplier interaction&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with and influence cross-functional teams to execute on the category strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-3 years of experience in a related field is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in distribution, online marketplaces, wholesale, e-commerce a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience analyzing data, building presentations and communicating effectively through data&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-sol

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: geist, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: geist, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Zoro.com is a leading eCommerce platform offering nearly 12 million tools, parts and supplies for our business customers. Launched in 2011, we brought a B2C-like experience to the B2B industry, and continue to be at the forefront of digital innovation at the intersection of technology and distribution. We have rapidly grown to over $1 billion in annual revenue and we’re just getting started!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Understanding our customers and delivering content that resonates with them is fundamental to the success of our business. The Customer Content Strategy Manager will coordinate the creation and execution of customer-aligned content and messaging strategies. This role is responsible for translating customer strategy into clear messaging hierarchies, defining content priorities by segment, and developing guidance for creative storytelling through vignettes and campaign assets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the development and alignment of customer messaging hierarchies across all segments, defining the most impactful content and messaging at each stage of the customer journey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strategic creative briefs that translate customer insights into clear messaging frameworks, content structures, and creative direction to drive consistent, targeted communication across channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and maintain a segment-driven content calendar, ensuring alignment with overarching content strategy across digital channels and web platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with creative and campaign teams to ensure execution is aligned with strategic intent and delivers cohesive storytelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross functionally with analytics teams to evaluate content performance, translating insights into actionable recommendations that continuously enhance the customer experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience with marketing planning/strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree or related professional experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated strategic thinking skills with a proven ability to develop, articulate, and execute effective strategies that drive business outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to measure performance and translate data into actionable objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience collaborating across various teams such as Creative Services, Analytics, Merchandising, and Execution teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration, communication, and organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to project manage/prioritize multiple projects simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter who thrives in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Rewards&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Zoro’s total compensation plan includes our Zoro Incentive Plan (ZIP) that is designed to foster and reward our team members for strong performance. Total compensation will be highly competitive.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
