&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: geist, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: geist, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Zoro.com is a leading eCommerce platform offering nearly 12 million tools, parts and supplies for our business customers. Launched in 2011, we brought a B2C-like experience to the B2B industry, and continue to be at the forefront of digital innovation at the intersection of technology and distribution. We have rapidly grown to over $1 billion in annual revenue and we’re just getting started!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Zoro, our competitive advantage is how we help customers discover what they need—and what they didn’t know they needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Storefront &amp;amp; Experience Strategy Lead, you will define and evolve how Zoro presents its assortment across key entry points, including the homepage, landing pages, and promotional storefronts. You’ll own the strategy behind how we guide customers through curated experiences that balance relevance, seasonality, and business priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of Merchandising, Marketing, and Product—ensuring that the storefront experience is both compelling and scalable, while reinforcing product discovery and conversion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define the strategy for Zoro’s storefront experiences, including homepage, landing pages, cross-category and campaign-driven experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish frameworks for how products and categories are surfaced based on customer context (e.g., seasonality, industry, behavior)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop scalable approaches to storefront merchandising, including content prioritization, placement logic, and personalization strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Marketing teams to translate campaigns and promotions into effective onsite experiences that drive engagement and conversion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Product partners to evolve storefront capabilities (e.g., CMS, personalization tools, testing frameworks) and improve flexibility and speed of execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define best practices for how storefront experiences connect to search, navigation, and category journeys to support end-to-end discovery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve storefront performance through better curation, relevance, and customer guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish standards to ensure consistency and quality across storefront experiences while enabling targeted differentiation where needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define success metrics (e.g., engagement, click-through rate, conversion, revenue per visit) and lead testing strategies to continuously optimize performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data, experimentation, and customer insights to refine storefront strategies and scale what works&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Category Experience and Global Experience Strategy teams to ensure alignment between storefront merchandising and broader discoverability systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5–8+ years of experience in ecommerce, digital merchandising, or onsite experience strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience owning or contributing to homepage, landing page, or campaign merchandising strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of how customers engage with curated experiences vs. search-driven journeys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to balance customer needs with business and promotional priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dat

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: geist, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.3;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: geist, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Zoro.com is a leading eCommerce platform offering nearly 12 million tools, parts and supplies for our business customers. Launched in 2011, we brought a B2C-like experience to the B2B industry, and continue to be at the forefront of digital innovation at the intersection of technology and distribution. We have rapidly grown to over $1 billion in annual revenue and we’re just getting started!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Zoro is seeking a Manager of Analytics &amp;amp; Insights to support how we measure, evaluate, and optimize the digital merchandising experience. This role will focus on analyzing performance across the customer funnel—from traffic and conversion to basket size—and translating data into actionable insights that improve the customer experience and drive business outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll play a key role in enabling a data-driven, test-and-learn culture by identifying trends, surfacing opportunities, and supporting decision-making. You’ll partner closely with teams across Merchandising, Marketing, Product, and Analytics to ensure insights are clear, actionable, and aligned to business priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze performance across Digital Merchandising, including traffic, conversion, AOV, and key business metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to KPI development, reporting frameworks, and measurement approaches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor performance and proactively detect anomalies, investigating root causes and summarizing findings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and support sizing of opportunities to improve the customer experience and drive business impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support regular performance reviews by synthesizing trends, tracking results against goals, and contributing to reporting materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare inputs and analysis for executive reporting, helping to translate data into clear insights and recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct customer insight and journey analysis, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Friction mapping to highlight areas of customer difficulty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Funnel analysis to identify drop-off points and performance trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience gap identification across the shopping journey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Segment behavior analysis to uncover differences in how customers shop&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Repeat purchase behavior and retention trend analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Merchandising to support test design and measurement, including analyzing results and delivering clear readouts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate data into structured insights and actionable recommendations to support decision-making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Merchandising, Marketing, Product, and Analytics teams to ensure alignment on data, reporting, and insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical thinker who can connect data to business questions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear communicator who can present insights in a structured and understandable way&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative and comfortable working with cross-functional partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curious and proactive, with a focus on identifying opportunities through data&lt;/li&gt;
