&lt;p&gt;The Pricing Analyst is responsible for supporting Zoro’s pricing and profitability strategy through pricing analysis, competitive monitoring, and performance reporting. This role analyzes pricing, sales, gross profit, customer behavior, and market data to identify opportunities that support revenue growth, margin performance, and competitive positioning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position partners with cross-functional teams to translate pricing insights into actionable business recommendations and support pricing initiatives across products and categories&lt;strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyzes pricing, sales, gross profit, customer behavior, and market trends to identify revenue and profitability opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitors competitor pricing and market dynamics to evaluate Zoro’s competitive position and support pricing decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluates product and category performance to identify pricing opportunities, competitive risks, and margin improvement actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports the development and execution of pricing strategies, including recommendations on where to match, lead, or differentiate from competitors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Builds and maintains recurring reports, dashboards, and monitoring tools that provide pricing and profitability insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Segments products into opportunity areas to prioritize actions that support business value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partners with Technology, Data Science, Category Management, Product, Finance, Marketing, and other teams on pricing analysis and initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Presents pricing findings and recommendations to stakeholders to support pricing initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
