&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience using analytics to solve business problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a subject matter expert in customer segments to gain a deep understanding of customer behavior that informs acquisition, activation, engagement, and retention strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for managing advanced analytical marketing projects and collaborating with internal business partners to support strategy development and tactic planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading the end to end analytical process: receive and evaluate business partners’ requests, develop an analytical plan and methodology, confirm analytical plans with business partners, implement data analyses, and provide recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide analytic support for key business activities (strategic initiatives, campaigns design, customer segmentation strategy, merchandising optimization etc.) including data mining, analysis,&amp;nbsp; presentations, and customer table development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead monthly review meetings to share insights/learning from the business data, and also provide updates on key analytical projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and make use of AI-driven systems (e.g., customer analysis automation) that connect AI agents to internal data pipelines and business workflows to drive customer insight&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years’ in progressive business experience in marketing analytics, database marketing, data mining, and statistical modeling. Experience with advanced data analysis in an ecommerce or a top-tier consumer-focused company (in technology, consumer goods or retail domain) are required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have prior

